> Shouldn't the search bar be aligned with title (in desktop version only)

I'm referring to the difference between:

![capture d ecran 2016-01-14 a 09 38 21](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2211145/12319489/f1d4d894-baa2-11e5-9e74-4525b287a0b8.png)

and:

![capture d ecran 2016-01-14 a 09 38 39](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2211145/12319490/f1d76f32-baa2-11e5-9b1f-9c8690700b59.png)

> This was done on purpose for three reasons. 1) When the search form and the button don't show a gap in the middle, the button looks like the Search button. I found myself several times clicking on that button when all I wanted is to search. 2) Removing the gap would mean to make the search input huge, and that usually looks wrong. 3) The gap allows to add more buttons to the "global actions" element, which is something that we'll allow in the future.

A simple separator or adding a `search` btn represented by a magnifier icon could solve this. Also the search bar width can be flexible (it'll always fill the available space, but won't prevent adding new "global actions")

